Super Eagles Manager, Gernot Rohr is confident that Nigeria will not lose its opening game against Croatia at the 2018 FIFA World Cup despite its 2-1 loss to England in a friendly at Wembley Stadium. The three-time African champions have lost twice in their last three warm-up matches. According to the German tactician, the one-time World Cup semifinalist are beatable. His words, “They are beatable. It is important that we take our first game 100% serious and secure the maximum three points. We have our game plan for each match and we will stick to it and take the group games as it comes.” Meanwhile, Croatia were beaten 2-1 by  Brazil at the Anfied stadium on Sunday afternoon in a friendly. Neymar and Roberto Firmino scored for Brazil. 